        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         This all goes back to when Verant was blurring the class lines and messing with titles, ie: Masters of Summoning, Masters of Magical Damage, Masters of Undead, etc.</P><P>For mages, believe it or not, they were not originally the masters of pets. Nobody was a master of pets. They were the masters of summoning. Thats why when Necros asked for a summon boneshard or dagger spell for our own pets, they told us that was the mages specialty. Thats why we only get to summon a pet and that weak little lightsource thing from level 1. Not exactly sure where this whole "We mages are the masters of pets" thing started. Think it was just before the class balance talks(the ones that never happened). </P><P>So for some reason (some not all)mages insist on believing that they are the masters of pets and nobody in the game has a right to have a pet even remotely as powerful. This is pretty much, fecal matter. I would think that having a pet at level 1 entitles a Necro to be considered as a pet class, and therefore gives us a right to have a well balanced pet in later levels. </P><P>Why constantly compare what a Necro has vs what a Mage doesnt have, yet continue to play your mage? If youre that unhappy, then start up a necro. So we have snares and FD and Mages dont. If it makes that much of an impact on your lives as to send you into a whirlwind of depression, then I would suggest that you start a different class...because guess what? Mages wont be getting snares or FD... ever(unless Verant begins to fold and just says fuck it and gives everyone every power known to Norrath). </P><P>And those tests...no logs, no parsing, no real fact, just hearsay. And they were done wrong. Pet vs pet was never a good way to guage a pets power and ability. If there was a level 59 Earth pet that procced a small DD, then Id say test them out. But there are level differences and resist levels that dont match up. Youll never get a consistant unbiased test doing pet vs pet.</P><P><img src="http://www.netset.com/~blazer/sig00b.jpg" border=0></P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
